  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nSeveral users reported an issue when trying to send an L2 Mainnet tx via MetaMask.\r\nThe default auto-calculated `gasLimit` and `gasPrice` appear to be too low, thus making txs fail if a user confirms a tx with the default values.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n1. Try to send some amount of ETH to another L2 address.\r\n2. See `gasPrice` and `gasLimit`\r\n3. Try sending tx with default values.\r\n4. Wait for confirmation or failing tx.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nDefault `gasLimit` and `gasPrice` values should not result in txs failing for users.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\nTaken from discord user messages:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"396\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-07-07 at 10 12 12 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37757724/124784712-cd7ba980-df0b-11eb-9709-97652c416825.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"466\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-07-07 at 10 22 35 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37757724/124786339-416a8180-df0d-11eb-8f25-9fae5dfab1b3.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nIssue came from reports in discord",
